The paper focuses on developing a method for filtering large quantities of software projects in a time-efficient way, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed method uses time-series clustering, which involves machine learning techniques such as k-means algorithm, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The study also involves processing metadata of GitHub repositories, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the study involves reducing hardware requirements, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
